## 📋 Requirements

### 🖥️ Hardware
- Intel Cyclone V FPGA Board  
- USB Blaster (for FPGA programming)  
- MQ-Series Gas Sensors (e.g., MQ-3, MQ-135) *(for future real-world testing)*  
- Power Supply Module  
- Breadboard & Connecting Wires  

---

### 💻 Software
- Quartus Prime (FPGA design & synthesis)  
- ModelSim (simulation & verification)  
- MATLAB / Python *(optional, for PCA validation & dataset generation)*  

---

### 🧠 Technical Knowledge
- Basic understanding of FPGA design (Verilog/VHDL)  
- Digital Signal Processing concepts  
- Principal Component Analysis (PCA)  
- Fixed-point arithmetic implementation  

---

### 📊 Data Requirements
- Synthetic or real VOC datasets (acetone, limonene levels)  
- Predefined threshold values for classification  

---

### ⚙️ System Specifications
- 8-channel sensor input support  
- Fixed-point PCA computation  
- Real-time processing at ~120 MHz  
